children.text: The bath has not been properly supported to prevent distortion and cracking.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3740 Waterproofing of Domestic Wet Areas, requires in clause 3.8 Baths and Spas that
‘Baths and spas shall be supported to prevent distortion and cracking’.
Additionally, the majority of bath manufacturers require that the base be supported under the full length of the floor of the bath, usually by a sand cement mortar bed;

The bases of these baths must be rectified to be properly supported in accordance with the Australian Standards and installation requirements specified by their manufacturer. Alternatively, the builder should provide evidence from the bath manufacturer that this method of support is acceptable.
